  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: b195a4e9a62f7ca41901229184c2c4fe, type: 3}
  m_Name: ZombieDialogue
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueModel
  description: This scriptable object contains all the needed info for the dialogue
    to play. The conversation list hold an object collection which contains the character
    information that tells the line and the line string.
  Conversation:
  - Line: '[interact] Kee...per... wait... my thumb fell into the potting soil again.
      Can you help me fish it out?'
    CharacterInfo: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 35b38d4930ae2fc42a77dfa9351932b3, type: 2}
  - Line: "[continue] Found it! I\u2019ll just pop it back on and wrap it with some
      fresh twine. You really need to stop over-watering yourself."
    CharacterInfo: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 5c997e2e5a0959546b5cd1b6b04fc4d9, type: 2}
  - Line: "[skip] But the ferns... they like the damp... and I don\u2019t mind a
      little extra moss in my pockets."
    CharacterInfo: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 35b38d4930ae2fc42a77dfa9351932b3, type: 2}
